Abiodun Nejo Ekiti State Government has approved the appointment of Prince Adeniyi Ajakaiye as the new Oluyin of Iyin-Ekiti in the Iropodun/Ifelodun Local Government Area of the state. The Oluyin stool became vacant on September 20, 2019 with the demise of the immediate past Oluyin, Justice Ademola Ajakaiye, from the only ruling house, Oketagidigidi Ruling House. The state government disclosed the new monarch’s approval in a statement by the Commissioner for Information, Mr Akin Omole, in Ado-Ekiti titled ‘Ekiti State Executive Council approves the appointment of Prince Adeola Adeniyi Ajakaiye as new Oluyin of Iyin-Ekiti.’ Copyright PUNCH.
